The paper deals with the problem of generalized phase retrieval, which is a fundamental task in various disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a geometric analysis of the problem and provides theoretical results that allow for efficient optimization methods. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to these sub-categories.
